text: Tracee Joy Silberstein (born October 29, 1972), known professionally as Tracee Ellis Ross, is an American actress, singer and television host. She is known for her lead roles in the television series Girlfriends (2000–2008) and Black- ish (2014–present). ==References== Category:1972 births Category:Living people Category:American movie actors Category:American television actors Category:American stage actors Category:American voice actors Category:American television presenters Category:Television personalities from Los Angeles Category:Singers from Los Angeles Category:Actors from Los Angeles
